label="Author's Name" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Kacy Leonce</Author><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>A total of 454 international students checked in at the International Services Office at the Spencer W. Kimball Building, the second greatest number of international students recorded on campus at BYU-Idaho.<br />Records show that in 2007 there were a total of 527 international students. During the following year, numbers dropped to 260 students before gradually increasing again. In 2009 there were 335 international students and 372<br />in 2010.<br />Although the numbers dropped in 2008, records show the number of international students are generally on the rise.<br />Mike Oswald, manager over the International Services Department, explained that although there is a total number of 454 students right now, these numbers are likely to drop during the semester because some students either transfer or drop out for various reasons.    <br />The recorded number of international students in any given semester is not finalized until halfway through<br />the semester.</p>
